<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="518" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1661,2010]" box="[199,1059,1769,1794]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1769,1794]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from the above-mentioned specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1661,2010]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner" authorityName="Hubner" box="[199,416,1805,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Calonotos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,314,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Calonotos</emphasis>
Hübner
</taxonomicName>
, [
<number box="[444,505,1806,1830]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" value="1819.0">1819</number>
] is a sexually dimorphic, moderately large genus, with around 
<number box="[1304,1332,1806,1830]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" value="20.0">20</number>
species, approximately half of which are part of a group of species with hyaline areas on the fore and hindwings. The limits of the species have never been examined, nor have the male-female associations, which are usually made only tentatively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1661,2010]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,392]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="518" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
<bibRefCitation author="Cerda" box="[199,347,1949,1974]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" refString="Cerda, J. - A. (2008) Euchromiini de Guyane Francaise (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae, Arctiinae). Published by the author, Place of publication unstated, 172 pp." type="book" year="2008">
Cerda (
<number box="[280,339,1950,1974]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
provided an illustration of the male genitalia of this species, of which he claimed to have seen the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1985,2010]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">holotype</typeStatus>
(error). However, it does match the genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[856,958,1985,2010]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[977,1064,1985,2010]" captionStart="FIGURES 55 – 65. 55" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1800,1822]" captionTargetBox="[230,1351,193,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[230,1351,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 55 – 65. 55) Eucyane variabilis flavofasciata, genitalia of the lectotype, dorsal view and phallus; 56) Diptilon crassum, genitalia of the holotype, ventral view and phallus; 57) Schasiura gymnelioides, genitalia of the holotype, ventral view and phallus; 58) Cercopimorpha hoffmanni, genitalia of a specimen from Tambopata, Peru, deposited at MZSP, dorsal view and phallus; 59) Eucereon lychnis, genitalia of the lectotype, lateral view and phallus; 60) Eucereon lychnis, genitalia of one of the female paralectotypes, lateral view; 61) Ceramidia pinguis, genitalia of the holotype, lateral view and phallus; 62) Eucereon sericeum, genitalia of the lectotype, ventral view and phallus; 63) Calonotos acutipennis, genitalia of the lectotype, lateral view and phallus; 64) Abrochia spitzi, genitalia of a specimen without locality deposited at MZSP, dorsal view and phallus; 65) Heliura zonata ab. aurantiaca, genitalia of Zerny’s male, dorsal view and phallus. Scale bars: 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240543/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
Fig. 
<number box="[1032,1064,1985,2010]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
). Additionally, Cerda mentioned that he could not pair any female with the male. The female 
<typeStatus box="[835,997,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1198,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Calonotos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutipennis">
<emphasis box="[1036,1198,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">C. acutipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
designated by Zerny were probably matched to the males by association with similar patterns of the hyaline areas of the hindwings, in pairs of other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[425,540,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Calonotos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[425,540,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">Calonotos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">
Both the male and female of this species closely resemble the established concept of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cramer, 1779" authorityName="Cramer" authorityYear="1779" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Calonotos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiburtus">
<emphasis box="[1203,1326,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">C. tiburtus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cramer" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" refString="Cramer, P. (1779 - 1780) Papillons exotiques des trois parties du monde, L'Asie, L'Afrique et l'Amerique. Vol. 3. S. J. Baalde, Utrecht, Barthelemy Wild, 176 pp. + plates 193 - 288." type="book chapter" year="1779">
Cramer, 
<number box="[151,211,296,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" value="1779.0">1779</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, illustrated in the original description and also by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson" box="[777,1164,295,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, vol. I: Catalogue of the Syntomidae in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 559 pp." type="book" year="1898">
Hampson (
<number box="[900,959,296,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" value="1898.0">1898</number>
, pp. 
<number box="[1012,1057,296,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" value="334.0">334</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[1113,1156,295,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" value="154.0">154</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and Draudt (
<number box="[1311,1370,295,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" value="1915.0">1915</number>
, plate 
<number box="[151,181,332,356]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" value="17.0">17</number>
, row i), which has 
<collectingCountry box="[393,488,332,357]" name="Suriname" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">Surinam</collectingCountry>
as its 
<typeStatus box="[558,606,333,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">type</typeStatus>
locality. The possibility that they are synonyms should be investigated, as it is unknown whether any 
<typeStatus box="[455,514,368,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[551,671,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Calonotos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiburtus">
<emphasis box="[551,671,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">C. tiburtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still exist.
</paragraph>
